The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 06 April is 265,873 (30,643.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 01 April, there were 6,830 new confirmed cases (787.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 March, there were 8,966 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 24% (2,136 fewer cases).
